Hampshire scored a convincing nine-wicket win in a rain-reduced match  against Essex at Southampton.
Robin Smith eased Hampshire home with a blistering 73 not out, supported  by his captain Mark Nicholas, who made 46 as Essex were beaten with 10 balls  to spare.
New England cap Shaun Udal trapped former England captain Graham Gooch,  caught at square-leg for 21, with his first ball, before bowling Paul  Pritchard at the start of the next over.
Opener John Stephenson kept Essex going with 47 off 43 balls, including  four fours, before he was bowled by Norman Cowans.
Nasser Hussain scored an unbeaten 30, supported by Mike Garnham, to lift  Essex to 124-3.
